Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} (double for 4p) into a medium #pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Cut the @broccolini{150%g} into thirds.

Stir the @coconut milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the @Diced Irish Chicken Breast{260%g} and onion, stirring occasionally, until the onion is softened and the chicken is golden brown on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Add the broccolini, then the garlic and @North Indian Style Spice Mix{2%sachets}.

Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Korma Curry Paste{1%sachet}, coconut milk, @Chicken Stock{1%sachet} and @water{25%ml} (double for 4p).

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Cover and simmer until sauce is slightly reduced, ~{7-9%minutes}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper. Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if you feel it's too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between #bowls{} alongside the chicken curry.

Serve the @Ballymaloe Tomato Relish{2%pots} on the side.